fields.description: *Assessment* Per AWS documentation regarding [ec2-import-keypair|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/CommandLineReference/ApiReference-cmd-ImportKeyPair.html], DSA keys are not supported. {code} DSA keys are not supported. Make sure your key generator is set up to create RSA keys. Supported lengths: 1024, 2048, and 4096. {code} When attempting to import DSA public keys on AWS, the following error is returned: {code} $ aws ec2 import-key-pair --key-name test-dsa --public-key-material /Users/haroldspencerjr/test_dsa.pub --profile harold-work A client error (InvalidKey.Format) occurred when calling the ImportKeyPair operation: Key is not in valid OpenSSH public key format {code} On Eucalyptus 3.4.2 and 4.0.0, the following is seen: * 3.4.2 {code} $ euca-import-keypair test-dsa --public-key-file test_dsa.pub --region account1-user01@ euca-import-keypair: fields.summary: Importing DSA Public Keypair Provides Vague Error

comments.body:
An InvalidKey.Format error now occurs for invalid key formats:

{code}
# ssh-keygen -t dsa -f test_dsa
Generating public/private dsa key pair.
Enter passphrase (empty for no passphrase): 
Enter same passphrase again: 
Your identification has been saved in test_dsa.
Your public key has been saved in test_dsa.pub.
The key fingerprint is:
af:90:f1:b3:dc:51:d7:da:53:33:26:da:52:71:2f:eb root@b-16.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com
The key's randomart image is:
+--[ DSA 1024]----+
|                 |
|                 |
|             . . |
|              o..|
|      . S   .oo++|
|       + . .+.o=+|
|      o o oo .o..|
|       o = ...  .|
|        + .   E  |
+-----------------+
#
#
# euca-import-keypair test-dsa --public-key-file test_dsa.pub
euca-import-keypair: error (InvalidKey.Format): Invalid or unsupported key format
{code}

Fix Verified

Installed Packages
Name        : eucalyptus
Arch        : x86_64
Version     : 4.0.0
Release     : 0.0.915.20140422git52eaefee.el6

Proper error returned for unsupported keypairs

invalid key length (768 in this case)
{code}
[root@h-20 ~]# euca-import-keypair -f long-key longkeypair

{code}

The key's randomart image is:
+--[ DSA 1024]----+
